hopobject.body: It's funny goodluck employment.westernhealth.nl.ca Haque made two more films in India, the 1857 mutiny drama The Rising: Ballad of Mangal Pandey (2005) and Hari Puttar: A Comedy of Terrors (2008), while consolidating her British stage and screen career. There was the role of the scheming Janoo Rani in a West End musical adaptation of The Far Pavilions (Shaftesbury Theatre, 2005) that closed after five months when the 7/7 London bombings resulted in audience figures plummeting. One critic predicted that she would become a "musical superstar".
